        <strong>Traveling Waves</strong> can be of any shape and move outward freely from a 
        source through a medium, carrying energy, but not 
        material. 
        A familiar example are waves propagating on the surface of water. 
        Traveling wave velocity is the product of frequency and wavelength (v = fÎ»).
